added.title: Butt Atoms
added.description: Despite Robin's warning, the Titans mess around with atomic toots and end up causing a worldwide plague.

added.title: The Zoo
added.description: Steven visits a special zoo.

added.title: Back to the Moon
added.description: Steven and the Gems revisit the Moon Base.

added.title: Story for Steven
added.description: Greg tells Steven the full story of how he met Rose-Quartz.

added.title: The Puppy
added.description: The kids finally get the puppy they always wanted, except . . . it's actually a turtle, and it hates them. After begging Dad for a puppy, the kids are taken aback when he comes home with a turtle. Despite the fact that the turtle turns out to be extremely aggressive (especially toward Gumball) they try their best to give it the love it deserves. This achieves nothing. The Evil Turtle escapes and goes on a rampage, and they have to find it before it destroys Elmore.

added.title: The Procrastinators
added.description: Gumball and Darwin go to extraordinary lengths to avoid taking out the trash. Gumball and Darwin are offended when Mom calls them "procrastinators", once she's told them what it means. They promise to take the trash out by the time she gets home. As the clock slowly counts down, they discover that they will go to extraordinary lengths, no matter how inane, to avoid the task in hand.

added.title: The Quest
added.description: Gumball and Darwin help Anais rescue her doll from Tina Rex.

added.title: The Pressure
added.description: Gumball tries to save Darwin from being kissed by a girl.

added.title: Glove Glove Me Do
added.description: Owen's newly found gloves make him great at everything. But this greatness comes at a high price.

added.title: Sand Trap
added.description: Axel and the team take to the desert dunes of a playground sandbox as Madcap attempts to unearth an army of Spy Lizards from the same line as Galileo!

added.title: Ener-G-Shoes
added.description: When Vic uses trickery to buy a pair of super cool sneakers from Maria Teresa's yard sale, the shoes try to walk him to his demise as punishment.

added.title: Free Chili
added.description: When Owen hides a walkie-talkie inside his chili dog, Harold believes it's an alien here to destroy Earth.

added.title: The News Never Sleeps!
added.description: Lil' Nelson takes a job as a paperboy, which is more difficult than it sounds in a city overrun by scorching Pyro Vipers and an evil Serpentine sorceress.

added.title: Ninja vs. Lava
added.description: The ninja find themselves trapped in a pyramid and must escape encroaching lava to warn NINJAGO City of a new Serpentine invasion.

added.title: Snaketastrophy
added.description: The Serpentine attack on NINJAGO City is seen from an unexpected perspective - entirely in the style of a live newscast delivered by Gayle Gossip and her cameraman.

added.title: Powerless
added.description: The ninja rush to the NINJAGO Museum of History to recover a dangerous scroll before it falls into the hands of the Serpentine Sorceress Aspheera.

added.title: Ancient History
added.description: While Aspheera pursues revenge on the "Treacherous Deceiver" who betrayed her, the ninja make a startling discovery.

added.title: Bobo Chan
added.description: Badgerclops adopts an abandoned monster, but some things are better left in the wild.

added.title: Small
added.description: Mao Mao's legendary, gigantic and critical father visits his son at his new job as sheriff.

added.title: Legend of Torbaclaun
added.description: When the Sweetypies think the mythical Torbaclaun has come to Pure Heart Valley, Mao Mao tries to prove to them that it isn't real.

added.title: Meet Tanya Keys
added.description: When bounty hunter Tanya Keys comes to town for Badgerclops, it's up to Mao Mao and Adorabat to save their friend -- even if he's been on the wrong side of the law.

added.title: Weapon of Choice
added.description: Worried that his sword is a glorified consolation prize, Mao Mao sets out to prove the worth of his weapon.

added.title: Stink Bomb
added.description: An accidental stink bomb explosion causes the kids to evacuate the Creek, but Craig takes it upon himself to rescue those left behind in the stench.

added.title: The Evolution of Craig
added.description: Craig rescues a tadpole and decides to raise him into a level 100 frog!

added.title: The Haunted Dollhouse
added.description: Craig and his friends find themselves being followed by a creepy doll and its haunted dollhouse.

added.title: Itch to Explore
added.description: Craig's quest to map the entire Creek takes him and his friends into the treacherous Poison Ivy Grove.

added.title: You're It
added.description: A vicious game of tag wreaks havoc on the Creek, claiming Kelsey as the next it.

added.title: Jessica Goes to the Creek
added.description: When Craig and Jessica are locked out of the house, Craig has no choice but to bring his little sister to the Creek.

added.title: The Final Book
added.description: The last book of Kelsey's favorite fantasy series goes missing from the library, so Craig decides to help her solve the mystery of who took it.

added.title: Too Many Treasures
added.description: Hoping to fix their fort, Craig enlists the 10 Speeds to give them a ride to the legendary Junk Pile.

added.title: Project Ray Way
added.description: When Raymond starts his own fashion line, Rad and Drupe decide to make something even better.

added.title: GarQuest
added.description: Gar and KO team up for a secret mission.

added.title: Glory Days
added.description: KO does a school report on Carol.

added.title: We Got Hacked
added.description: Dendy helps KO, Enid and Rad stop a glitch that threatens to take over the bodega.

added.title: Back in Red Action
added.description: Enid teams up with Red Action to take on a menace from the future.

added.title: Ice Cream Headache
added.description: The campers get magical powers from the witches supply of magic ice cream.

added.title: Pepper's Blanket Is Missing
added.description: Pepper's blanket goes missing at a cabin sleepover.

added.title: Hedgehog Werewolf
added.description: Hedgehog gets bit by a cute puppy and is starting to act strange.

added.title: Mr. Softball
added.description: Susie challenges the campers to a game of softball to get out of doing a chore.

added.title: Fuzzy Pink Time Babies
added.description: Oscar and Hedgehog learn how to stop time.

added.title: Orgalorg
added.description: After a walrus race accident, Gunther starts to experience strange visions.

added.title: Mystery Dungeon
added.description: Ice King, NEPTR, Tree Trunks, Shelby and Lemongrab are trapped inside a mysterious dungeon and must work together to free themselves.

added.title: Cartoon Factory
added.description: Uncle Grandpa visits the cartoon factory to get some answers about his roots.

added.title: Goodbye and Good Riddance
added.description: Summer's over and Ben is back at school. Unable to tell anyone that's he all these cool aliens that they've heard about all summer, Ben suddenly realizes he's gone from a "hero" to a "zero", that is until Vilgax comes after him with a vengeance. Ben must now reveal his hero side to his parents and to his fellow classmates. In doing so he saves his town and teams up with his dad to destroy Vilgax once and for all. But there is some bad news...Gwen has switched schools and is in Ben's class!

added.title: A Gift for Gus
added.description: Uncle Grandpa's present for Mr. Gus gets loose and causes trouble.

added.title: Clarence and Sumo's Rexcellent Adventure
added.description: On a school trip to the Aberdale Natural History Museum, Clarence and Sumo check out the displays, goof around with the exhibits and even remove a tooth from the T-Rex display.

added.title: Fishing Trip
added.description: Mel learns that Chad has never taken Clarence fishing, a tradition he sees as a rite of passage, and decides to remedy this with a bonding trip for all the boys! Split into two groups, Mel and Clarence learn a bit about each other while Chad struggles with the ins and outs of fishing.

added.title: Ragnarock and Roll
added.description: When an ancient prophecy spells doom for Townsville, the girls must race to stop it.

added.title: Ren Faire
added.description: Clarence and his pals venture to the Aberdale Renaissance Faire. Clarence confuses a medieval play for reality, and vows to stop the evil black knight from getting the princess.

added.title: They Lurk Below
added.description: Max's old friend has built the world's only underwater resort, and Ben, Gwen and Max are invited for a sneak peak. But it turns out in order to power the resort, Max's friend took an energy orb from a race of underwater aliens. Now, the aliens want their energy orb back and destroy the resort in order to get it.

added.title: Take Your Kids to Dooms Day
added.description: The Girls spend the day with the Professor at his boring office, only to find that the office comes with a terrible secret.

added.title: The Crossroads Part 1
added.description: An attempt to use a derelict SpaceBridge sends The Ark to Unspace!

added.title: The Crossroads Part 2
added.description: Optimus and the Autobots team up with some very familiar faces to escape Unspace.

added.title: Honk
added.description: Seeking to improve his communication skills, Clarence turns to a squeeze horn. It's really annoying.

added.title: For a Few Brains More
added.description: Ben, Rook and Max must stop Ultimate Albedo from absorbing Azmuth's intelligence and taking over the galaxy.

added.title: Animo Crackers
added.description: Dr. Animo from the future comes back to the present to help himself defeat Ben once and for all. (Introducing new Ben alien, Gutrot.)

added.title: Charmed, I'm Sure
added.description: Still stranded on the monster planet Anur Transyl, Ben and Rook reluctantly team up with Charmcaster to take on Zs' Skayr.

added.title: Catfight
added.description: The princesses Looma and Attea are at odds over who gets to marry Ben!

added.title: A New Dawn
added.description: The Time War brings Ben, Rook, and George Washington together to battle an alien conqueror.

added.title: Power Cycle
added.description: After replicating Elec Man's powers, an underslept/overcharged Mega Man goes on a 24/7 hero spree that ends up turning him into his own worst enemy.

added.title: Bored to Be Wild
added.description: Mega Man teams up with his crush, Ashley Adderley, to solve a series of science riddles left by Chemical Man, who's plotting to turn all the city's metal into rubber.

added.title: Enter the Wood Man
added.description: Mega Man accidentally awakens Wood Man, who thinks it's still the Hard Age, sets off on a path of destruction toward Silicon City.

added.title: Lightfall Part 1
added.description: The mysterious Lord Obsidian calls Mega Man a traitor to robots and challenges him to a duel. An overconfident Mega Man is humbled by this mysterious new villain.

added.title: Lightfall Part 2
added.description: Lord Obsidian attacks the Lighthouse, but Mega Man overcomes his insecurity and works with his family to repel the big bad, who's rescued at the last second by a mysterious lieutenant, Namagem.

added.title: Chile libre
added.description: Cuando Owen oculta un walkie talky dentro de su perro con chile, Harold cree que es un alienígena que vino a destruir la tierra.

added.title: Las Noticias Nunca Duermen
added.description: Lil 'Nelson toma un trabajo como repartidor de periódicos, lo cual es más difícil de lo que parece en una ciudad invadida por Pyro Vipers y una malvada hechicera serpentina.

added.title: Ninja Contra Lava
added.description: Los ninja se encuentran atrapados en una pirámide y deben escapar de la lava invasora para advertir a la ciudad de NINJAGO de una nueva invasión serpentina.

added.title: Serpientastrofe
added.description: El ataque de Serpentine en NINJAGO City se ve desde una perspectiva inesperada, completamente al estilo de un noticiero en vivo entregado por Gayle Gossip y su camarógrafo.

added.title: Intolerancia Heladil
added.description: Los campistas obtienen poderes mágicos gracias a la reserva de helado mágico de las brujas.

added.title: La Desaparicion de la Manta de Peper
added.description: La manta de Pepper desaparece en una pijamada en la cabaña.

added.title: Erizo Nina Lobo
added.description: A Hedgehog lo muerde un perrito tierno y comienza a comportarse de manera extraña.

added.title: Mister Softbol
added.description: Susie desafía a los campistas a jugar un partido de softball para librarse de una tarea.

added.title: Peludos Bebes Rosas del Tiempo
added.description: Oscar y Erizo aprenden a detener el tiempo.
